### Blogo API Examples
### Use with REST Client extensions in VS Code or any HTTP client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/ping

### ==================== USER ENDPOINTS ====================

### Create New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/u/new
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "display_name": "John Doe"
}

### Create Another User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/u/new
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "janedoe",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "display_name": "Jane Doe"
}

### Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/u/1

### Update User Profile (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/u/1/manage
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "display_name": "John Smith",
  "bio": "Software developer and blogger",
  "profile_image": "https://example.com/profile.jpg"
}

### Follow User (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/u/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "follow"
}

### Unfollow User (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/u/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "unfollow"
}

### Get User's Followers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/u/1/follows?limit=20&offset=0

### Get Users a User is Following
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/u/1/following?limit=20&offset=0

### ==================== BLOG ENDPOINTS ====================

### Get All Blogs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/b?limit=10&offset=0

### Get Blog by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/b/1

### Create New Blog (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/new
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Getting Started with Go",
  "description": "A beginner's guide to Go programming",
  "body": "Go is an open source programming language that makes it easy to build simple, reliable, and efficient software. In this post, we'll explore the basics..."
}

### Create Another Blog (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/new
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Why I Love Blogging",
  "description": "My thoughts on content creation",
  "body": "Blogging has been an incredible journey. It allows me to share my thoughts, connect with others, and document my learning process..."
}

### Update Blog (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/1/edit
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Getting Started with Go - Updated",
  "description": "An updated beginner's guide to Go programming",
  "body": "Go is an open source programming language... [Updated content here]"
}

### Delete Blog (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/1/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Like Blog (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "like"
}

### Unlike Blog (Authenticated)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "unlike"
}

### Get Blog Likes
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/b/1/likes?limit=20&offset=0

### ==================== PAGINATION EXAMPLES ====================

### Get Blogs with Pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/b?limit=5&offset=0

### Get Next Page of Blogs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/b?limit=5&offset=5

### ==================== ERROR EXAMPLES ====================

### Unauthorized Request (No Token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/new
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should fail",
  "body": "Because no auth token is provided"
}

### Invalid Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/b/new
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should also fail",
  "body": "Because the token is invalid"
}

### Invalid Request Body
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/u/new
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "test"
}


